lyrics.stanza:
"Almost persuaded" now to believe;
"Almost persuaded" Christ to receive;
  Seems now some soul to say,
  "Go, Spirit, go Thy way,
  Some more convenient day
    on Thee I'll call."

"Almost persuaded," come, come today;
"Almost persuaded," turn not away;
  Jesus invites you here,
  Angels are ling'ring near,
  Prayers rise from hearts so dear;
    O wand'rer, come!

Oh, be persuaded! Christ never fails&mdash;
Oh, be persuaded! His blood avails&mdash;
  Can save from every sin,
  Cleanse you without, within&mdash;
  Will you not let Him in?
    Open the door!

"Almost persuaded," harvest is past!
"Almost persuaded," doom comes at last;
  "Almost" cannot avail;
  "Almost" is but to fail!
  Sad, sad that bitter wail&mdash;
    "Almost&mdash;but lost!"

Be now persuaded, oh, sinner, hear!
Be now persuaded, Jesus is near;
  His voice is pleading still,
  Turn now with heart and will,
  Peace will your spirit fill&mdash;
    Oh, turn today!
